- C = 90 µF  
- V₀ = 1000 V  
- L = 22 nH  
- Target: I_peak < 4.2 kA  

The theoretical maximum current in an ideal LC circuit would be I_max = V₀ × √(C/L) ≈ 6.4 kA—well above your limit. However, with resistive damping factored via `R_erosion_coeff`, we can suppress the peak.  

